<h1>Feline</h1>
<img src="https://i.postimg.cc/j51KLPxv/catimage.jpg" alt="Cat Image">
<p><em>Cats can purr both when they inhale and exhale.</em> <br>
<br>
<strong>Scientific Name:</strong> Felis catus
<br><strong>Average Length:</strong> 18 inches
<br><strong>Average Lifespan:</strong> 15 years
<br><strong>Habitat:</strong> For cats, their natural habitat includes a range of environments, <br> from deserts to forests, and from grasslands to wetlands.
<br>
<br>Commonly referred to as the domestic cat or house cat, is a small carnivorous mammal.
<br>Cats have highly developed senses, including excellent hearing and sense of smell.
<br>They can see better than humans in dark and dim light.
<br>Cats are expert hunters. In the wild they'll spend 6-8 hours a day hunting. <br>
Domesticated cats have been tamed for nearly 10,000 years. 

